-- Bayer, Delticom, Dialog, MorphoSys, Volkswagen: German Equity Preview
-- Julie Cruz
-- 2010-07-20T06:38:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/bayer-delticom-dialog-morphosys-volkswagen-equity-preview-for-germany.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Germany. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 The benchmark DAX Index lost 0.5 percent to 6,009.11
yesterday. DAX Index futures expiring in September rose 0.5
percent to 6,049 as of 8:19 a.m. in Frankfurt.  
 Bayer AG  (BAYN GY): Bayer CropScience Ltd.’s shares surged
in Mumbai after the maker of agrochemicals said it plans to sell
about 100 acres of land. Bayer shares dropped 0.2 percent to
46.21 euros in Frankfurt.  
 Delticom AG  (DEX GY): The tire dealer said first-half
earnings before interest and taxes rose 62 percent to 16.5
million euros ($21.5 million), as revenue increased 27 percent.
The shares declined 0.8 percent to 38.51 euros.  
 Dialog Semiconductor Plc  (DLG GY): The semiconductor maker
confirmed its 2010 forecast as it reported second-quarter net
income of $11.2 million. The shares surged 3.3 percent to 10.91
euros.  
 MorphoSys AG  (MOR GY): The drugmaker is examining potential
acquisition targets in the field of diagnostics though a
transaction may not come to fruition this year, Boersen Zeitung
reported, citing an interview with Chief Executive Officer  Simon Moroney . The shares rose 0.9 percent to 15 euros.  
 Volkswagen AG  (VOW3 GY): The carmaker’s money-losing U.S.
unit will be profitable “shortly,” Chief Executive Officer
 Martin Winterkorn  told reporters in Palo Alto, California. The
shares lost 1.8 percent to 74.63 euros.  
